cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper deals with the problem of reliable sensing of low power licensed users in dynamic spectrum access systems, which is a key issue in the field of information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The specific scenario of unlicensed use of TV bands also falls under the category of communication and networking (cs.CR). The development of a sub-space algorithm for signal detection involves system control and optimization (cs.SY). Finally, the use of wireless microphones in TV white space has implications for multimedia systems and applications (cs.MM).
